\f2\fs20 \cf0 In recognition of the 15th year of the Tech 50 Awards, the Pittsburgh Technology Council stepped up its own technological efforts Wednesday when announcing the finalists.
\f3\fs24 \

\f2\fs20 The awards honor the Pittsburgh region's fastest growing and most innovative tech companies.
\f3\fs24 \

\f2\fs20 About 15 corporate sponsors gathered in the PTC Resource Room, at the council's offices in South Oakland, to hear the announcement of this year's Tech 50 finalists, while 60 more people watched via webcast for the first time through Concert-Oh, a Monroeville-based Web teleconferencing company. The Pittsburgh Post-Gazette is a media sponsor for the Tech 50 Awards.
\f3\fs24 \

\f2\fs20 The Technology Council also unveiled a video contest that encourages companies to download amateur videos about their offices to YouTube. The top three videos will be judged during the Tech 50 awards in September, where attendees will vote for winners via text message.
\f3\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl260\sb240\qj\partightenfactor0

